content.description: Climb the face just right of the small cave, ending on the right side of the bulge at the top.  Pretty good rock.
content.protection: Bolts, 2 bolt anchor.  Rap or lower.
content.location: Near the right end of the Paddlefish Wall, this is the second route from the right.  Start just right of the small cave and end on the right side of the bulge up top.

content.description: Low, tricky crux on face climbing, then sustained at a slightly moderate level.

Climb past the first few bolts on Jeronimo and step left into the right facing dihedral crack.  Make sure to place long slings before and after going into the corner, as it is sharp.  Follow the dihedral crack up and right.  Where it ends, traverse right to bolted anchors on another route.  Pretty good rock.
content.protection: Bolts, gear to 2", slings.  2 bolt anchor.  Rap or lower.
content.location: Start on the first bolted line on the left of the Paddlefish Wall, Jeronimo.

content.description: Climb the face starting on the left side of the cave and ending on the left side of the bulge at the top.  Pretty good rock.
content.protection: Bolts, 2 bolt anchor.  Rap or lower.
content.location: Near the right end of the Paddlefish Wall, this route starts on the left side of the small cave.  3rd line from the right.

content.description: Climb the technical vertical face and steep slab above on pretty good rock.
content.protection: Bolts, 2 bolt anchor.  Rap or lower.
content.location: Near the middle of the Paddlefish Wall, this is the 4th bolted line from the right.

content.description: Vertical face and steep slab climbing on pretty good rock.  If I remember right, there are both a mono and a cool fingerlock on this route.
content.protection: Bolts, 2 bolt anchor.  Rap or lower.
content.location: Near the middle of the Paddlefish Wall, this is the second line left of the small cave.

content.description: Start under two large huecos and face climb through crimps, jugs, and underclings below the small overlap. Two solutions exist, leading to separate clipping stances, onto the upper slab. A few friction moves takes you to the anchors on good holds.
content.protection: 6 Bolts. Fixed steel lower off anchor. Stick-clip.
content.location: Leftmost route on Paddlefish Wall. Left of Jeronimo and Shadow Puppet.

content.description: Face climbing on decent quality vertical rock.
content.protection: Bolts, 2 bolt anchor.  Rap or lower.
content.location: Near the middle of the Paddlefish Wall, this is the first bolt line left of the small cave.

content.description: First route right of the cave/alcove. Climb to a roof, then follow the arête/face to anchors.
content.location: Far left end of Paddlefish wall before hiking towards Little Long Dog Wall

content.description: Blank face with many unique mini-cruxes right of the Shadow Puppet dihedral.

Stick-clip the first bolt and pull several moves off the ground to reach it. Cruise for a brief section into a crux of side-pulls, friction, and bad feet aiming for the softball sized pocket up and left. Hold it together and piece deceiving slab until you reach good holds and cruise to the anchor pillar.
content.protection: 5 Bolts. Fixed steel lower off anchor. Stick-Clip.
content.location: This is the rightmost route on Paddlefish Wall. Right of Billy Bob Bulldozer. Left of the archway and Beringia.

content.description: Climb the low-angled slab to a chossy ledge.  Then continue on better rock through the blocky bulge up high to the anchors.  Half the route is pretty good rock, the other half is pretty chossy.
content.location: The farthest bolted route to the right on the Long Dog Wall.  This route starts left of the small cave and under the large block up high.

content.description: Start down and right of a large hueco that gets you to the first bolt. A variety pockets and crimps lend to a positive horizontal setting up for stance, that fires through a series of small crimps and side-pulls past the namesake feature and into a few more slab moves finishing on the upper block.
content.location: After the standard walk-down approach there is a natural arch cave feature. This route is located on an isolated wall between the archway and the walk-down.

content.description: This area's conditions are the same as the Long Dog Wall.
